Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of tensor-network techniques in machine learning, specifically for probabilistic modeling. This makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of hidden Markov models, which falls under cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of tensor networks for enhancing the mathematical understanding of existing methods suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the tractability of likelihoods and efficient learning algorithms, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the use of tensor networks for local quantum circuits, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
